8TH SEM-ELE4- CRYPTOGRAPHY AND NETWORK SECURITY (CNS-ec) starts on 2023-02-16.

Students will be able to

1. Recognize the essential components and principles of cryptography;

2. Describe the fundamental principles and application of symmetric encryption and cryptographic hashing to

provide an improved cyber security measure.

3. describe the fundamental principles and application of asymmetric and public-key encryption and a Public-Key

Infrastructure (PKI) to provide an improved cyber security measure;

4. Implement the application of cryptographic techniques and protocols to protect the transmission and storage of

information, provide confidentiality, integrity, protected message exchanges, data origin authentication, entity

authentication and non-repudiation; Identify and explain key management, digital signatures and digital

certificates

5. Describe network security applications, password management, Firewall, IDS, Web security, Email security,

and malicious software etc.

8TH SEM-ELE4 - ERROR CONTROL CODING (ECC) starts on 2023-02-16.

Upon Completion of the course students will be able to

1. Students will be able to apply the knowledge of linear algebra for various codes.

2. Students will be able to design linear block codes and cyclic codes.

3. Students will be able to analyze the basics of error control codes.

4. Students will be able to apply various algorithms to design the encoder and decoder circuit of

error control codes.

5. Students will be able to illustrate the characteristic features and capability of different error

control codes.

1. Learn the various categories of Multimedia and Networks
2. Analyze and select the network and signal form for various multimedia applications
3. Analyze and apply compression schemes for different Multimedia
4. Gain knowledge of various standards used for Compression, Multiplexing and Networks
5. Evaluate the Security aspects of Multimedia communications

AY_23_24_Sem3_22MBASC302_ E- Supply_ Chain _Management (AY_23_24_Sem3_22MBASC302_ESCM) starts on 2023-10-29.

Course Objectives:

  • To enable students to learn the role of IT in supply chain
  • To provide conceptual and application of supply chain information system design
  • To analyze the various IT practices in supply chain.
  • To understand human aspects in technology management

Course Outcomes: At the end of the course, students will be able to:

  • Apply knowledge of supply chain theories and practices to solve business problems.
  • Understand the various information technology practices in supply chain and apply in decision making.
  • Analyze the impact of IT on logistics decisions, performance of firm as well as entire supply chain in global, economic, legal, and ethical aspects of business.
  • Apply the various e-logistics tools for better logistics management.

Aircraft Desigh and Analysis-A (ADA_A) starts on 2024-09-19.

Objective: This course provides foundational knowledge and practical skills in designing and analyzing aircraft. It covers the full lifecycle of aircraft development, including conceptual design, aerodynamic considerations, structural analysis, and performance evaluation.

Key Topics

  1. Introduction to Aircraft Design

    • Overview of the design process: concept, design, testing, and certification.
    • Roles of aerospace engineers and design teams.

  2. Conceptual Design

    • Mission requirements and design constraints.
    • Aircraft configuration selection: wing, tail, fuselage, landing gear, and propulsion layouts.
    • Design trade-offs: range, speed, payload, and cost considerations.

  3. Aerodynamics and Lift Generation

    • Basic aerodynamics principles: lift, drag, and stability.
    • Airfoil selection and wing design.
    • Computational methods in aerodynamic analysis.

  4. Propulsion Systems

    • Overview of propulsion options (jet, propeller, turbofan).
    • Engine integration and thrust considerations.

  5. Structural Analysis

    • Structural design principles: weight, strength, and safety.
    • Material selection and stress analysis.
    • Structural testing methods.

  6. Performance and Stability

    • Performance metrics: climb rate, speed, range, and endurance.
    • Stability and control analysis: static and dynamic stability.
    • Design for maneuverability and control.

  7. Weight and Balance

    • Weight distribution and its impact on stability.
    • Center of gravity (CG) considerations and calculation methods.

  8. Aircraft Systems and Avionics

    • Overview of critical aircraft systems: hydraulic, electrical, fuel, and landing gear.
    • Introduction to avionic systems for navigation, communication, and flight control.

  9. Environmental and Regulatory Considerations

    • Noise, emissions, and regulatory compliance.
    • Certification standards (FAA, EASA) and design impact.

  10. Design Project and Case Studies

    • Practical design projects integrating course concepts.
    • Analysis of existing aircraft designs and innovations.

Students will be able to:

1. Describe the conceptual design process of an aircraft, airfoil, and wing geometry.

2. Describe initial sizing and configuration layout.

3. Illustrate the application of aerodynamics, propulsion, and aircraft structures in design.

4. Discuss the design aspects of sub systems in flight vehicles.

Welcome to "Scientific Foundations of Health"

The scientific foundations of health provide the essential framework for understanding the intricate mechanisms of the human body and how it interacts with the environment. Through rigorous research and evidence-based practices, this field enables advancements in medicine, public health, and healthcare policies, ultimately contributing to the well-being of individuals and populations worldwide.

It's not a subject to just GO through and clear the exams for a credit score of 1 point, but imbibes and inculcates values to GROW through, to attain healthy and happy professional and social well-being.
